cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.SE. 

The paper discusses Answer Set Programming (ASP), which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (AI) that deals with logic-based knowledge representation and reasoning. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces new algorithms for computing cautious consequences, which involves logical reasoning and can be categorized under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). The algorithms also make use of unsatisfiable cores computation, which is a technique used in constraint solving and falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation and experiments on benchmarks, which can be categorized under cs.SE (Software Engineering).
